{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891141442,"sessionID":"ses_284a3f4d3ffe8bFOTfB7U7JhyS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b5c42e4001YSR6XhYfgOKfL5","messageID":"msg_d7b5c38f90014Sja2hQKu99nyS","sessionID":"ses_284a3f4d3ffe8bFOTfB7U7JhyS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_341a5370ceb94ba8816aad7b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n8: 2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n9: 3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n10: 4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n11: 5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n12: \n13: This implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** M\n20: \n21: This AR covers:\n22: \n23: - **In scope:**\n24:   - Core `PicoD` struct and initialization (`picod.go`)\n25:   - Command execution logic with resource limits (`executor.go`)\n26:   - Resource limit configuration and enforcement (`limits.go`)\n27:   - Output capture and streaming (`output.go`)\n28:   - Security validations and sandboxing (`security.go`)\n29:   - Unit tests with mocked executors\n30:   - Integration tests with real command execution\n31:   - Configuration via environment variables\n32: \n33: - **Out of scope:**\n34:   - Container runtime integration (covered in AR-005, AR-009)\n35:   - Network namespace manipulation\n36:   - User namespace management\n37:   - Filesystem isolation beyond chroot/workspace jail\n38:   - Distributed command execution\n39:   - PicoD HTTP daemon (covered in `code-execution/` specs)\n40: \n41: ## Current State Analysis\n42: \n43: ### Existing Sandbox Infrastructure\n44: \n45: The current system has sandbox management infrastructure:\n46: \n47: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`):\n48:    - Creates and manages sandbox pods\n49:    - Handles lifecycle (create, update, delete)\n50:    - Supports warm pool for pre-provisioned sandboxes\n51: \n52: 2. **CodeInterpreter CRD** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`):\n53:    - Defines `CodeInterpreterSpec` with image, command, args, env, resources\n54:    - Supports `AuthMode` enum (`picod` or `none`)\n55:    - Default image: `volcanosh/picod:latest`\n56: \n57: 3. **Workload Manager**:\n58:    - Handles `CodeInterpreter` resources\n59:    - Creates underlying sandbox pods\n60:    - Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode=picod`\n61: \n62: ### Gaps Identified\n63: \n64: 1. **No unified execution API** - Command execution logic is scattered or non-existent\n65: 2. **No resource limit enforcement** - No programmatic way to enforce CPU/memory/time limits\n66: 3. **No output streaming** - Cannot stream output for long-running commands\n67: 4. **No security hardening** - Missing input validation and sandboxing at the API level\n68: 5. **No cancellation support** - Cannot gracefully cancel running commands\n69: \n70: ### PicoD Context\n71: \n72: Per `code-execution/design.md` and `code-execution/spec.md`:\n73: - PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail\n74: - Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n75: - CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default: current working directory)\n76: - Server uses `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n77: \n78: ## Proposed Changes\n79: \n80: ### 1. Core PicoD Structure (`picod.go`)\n81: \n82: ```go\n83: // PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\n84: type PicoD struct {\n85:     sandboxID    string\n86:     workDir      string\n87:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n88:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n89:     logger       klog.Logger\n90: }\n91: \n92: // Option is a functional option for PicoD\n93: type Option func(*PicoD)\n94: \n95: // New creates a new PicoD instance\n96: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n97: \n98: // WithWorkDir sets the working directory\n99: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n100: \n101: // WithLimits sets resource limits\n102: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n103: \n104: // WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n105: func WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n106: \n107: // WithLogger sets the logger\n108: func WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ### 2. Resource Limits (`limits.go`)\n112: \n113: ```go\n114: // ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\n115: type ResourceLimits struct {\n116:     // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n117:     Timeout time.Duration\n118:     \n119:     // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n120:     MaxCPU float64\n121:     \n122:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n123:     MaxMemory int64\n124:     \n125:     // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n126:     MaxOutputSize int64\n127:     \n128:     // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n129:     MaxProcesses int\n130: }\n131: \n132: // DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\n133: func DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n134: \n135: // Validate validates resource limits\n136: func (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### 3. Security Options (`security.go`)\n140: \n141: ```go\n142: // SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\n143: type SecurityOptions struct {\n144:     // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n145:     UID int\n146:     \n147:     // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n148:     GID int\n149:     \n150:     // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n151:     Capabilities []string\n152:     \n153:     // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n154:     ReadOnlyFS bool\n155:     \n156:     // NoNetwork disables network access\n157:     NoNetwork bool\n158:     \n159:     // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n160:     AllowedCommands []string\n161: }\n162: \n163: // DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\n164: func DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n165: \n166: // Validate validates security options\n167: func (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### 4. Command Execution API (`executor.go`)\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: // Command represents a command to execute\n174: type Command struct {\n175:     // Path is the command path\n176:     Path string\n177:     \n178:     // Args are the command arguments\n179:     Args []string\n180:     \n181:     // Env is the environment variables\n182:     Env []string\n183:     \n184:     // Dir is the working directory\n185:     Dir string\n186:     \n187:     // Stdin is the standard input\n188:     Stdin io.Reader\n189:     \n190:     // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n191:     Stdout io.Writer\n192:     \n193:     // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n194:     Stderr io.Writer\n195: }\n196: \n197: // CommandResult represents the result of command execution\n198: type CommandResult struct {\n199:     // ExitCode is the process exit code\n200:     ExitCode int\n201:     \n202:     // Stdout is the captured standard output\n203:     Stdout []byte\n204:     \n205:     // Stderr is the captured standard error\n206:     Stderr []byte\n207:     \n208:     // Duration is the execution duration\n209:     Duration time.Duration\n210:     \n211:     // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n212:     OOMKilled bool\n213:     \n214:     // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n215:     Timeout bool\n216: }\n217: \n218: // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n219: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n220: \n221: // Start starts a command without waiting\n222: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n223: \n224: // Process represents a running process\n225: type Process struct {\n226:     // PID is the process ID\n227:     PID int\n228:     \n229:     // Wait waits for the process to complete\n230:     Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n231:     \n232:     // Kill sends a signal to the process\n233:     Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n234: }\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ### 5. Output Streaming (`output.go`)\n238: \n239: ```go\n240: // OutputHandler handles streaming output\n241: type OutputHandler interface {\n242:     // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n243:     OnStdout(data []byte)\n244:     \n245:     // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n246:     OnStderr(data []byte)\n247:     \n248:     // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n249:     OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n250: }\n251: \n252: // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n253: func (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### 6. Security Validation (`security.go`)\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: // ValidateCommand validates a command for security\n260: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n261: \n262: // IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\n263: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n264: \n265: // DropPrivileges drops privileges to the specified UID/GID\n266: func DropPrivileges(uid, gid int) error\n267: \n268: // SetResourceLimits applies resource limits to the current process\n269: func SetResourceLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) error\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ### 7. Configuration\n273: \n274: #### Environment Variables\n275: \n276: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n277: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n278: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n279: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n280: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n281: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n282: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n283: | `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n284: \n285: ### 8. Error Handling\n286: \n287: ```go\n288: // ExecutionError represents an execution error\n289: type ExecutionError struct {\n290:     // Type is the error type\n291:     Type ExecutionErrorType\n292:     \n293:     // Message is the error message\n294:     Message string\n295:     \n296:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n297:     Underlying error\n298: }\n299: \n300: type ExecutionErrorType string\n301: \n302: const (\n303:     ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n304:     ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n305:     ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n306:     ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n307:     ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n308:     ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n309: )\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ## Impact Analysis\n313: \n314: ### Dependencies\n315: \n316: | Package | Purpose |\n317: |---------|---------|\n318: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n319: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n320: | `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n321: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n322: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n323: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n324: \n325: ### Affected Components\n326: \n327: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n328: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n329: 3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n330: 4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n331: 5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n332: \n333: ### Backward Compatibility\n334: \n335: - This is a new module with no existing API surface\n336: - No breaking changes to existing components\n337: - Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n338: - Existing `CodeInterpreter` CRD already references PicoD image\n339: \n340: ### Risk Assessment\n341: \n342: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n343: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n344: | Command injection | Low | High | Input validation, allowlist-based command selection |\n345: | Resource exhaustion | Medium | High | Enforce strict CPU/memory/time limits |\n346: | Privilege escalation | Low | Critical | Run as non-root, drop capabilities, use namespaces |\n347: | Output buffer overflow | Low | Medium | Stream large outputs, enforce size limits |\n348: | Zombie processes | Medium | Low | Proper process reaping, signal handling |\n349: \n350: ## Alternatives Considered\n351: \n352: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing Library (e.g., go-execute, bazel-remote)\n353: \n354: **Approach**: Leverage existing command execution libraries\n355: \n356: **Pros**:\n357: - Less code to maintain\n358: - Battle-tested implementations\n359: - Community support\n360: \n361: **Cons**:\n362: - May not meet specific security requirements for sandboxed execution\n363: - Additional dependency management overhead\n364: - Less control over resource limit enforcement\n365: - May not support Kubernetes-native patterns\n366: \n367: **Decision**: Implement custom solution for full control over security and limits, and better integration with AgentCube architecture.\n368: \n369: ### Alternative 2: Shell-based Execution\n370: \n371: **Approach**: Execute commands via `/bin/sh -c`\n372: \n373: **Pros**:\n374: - Simple implementation\n375: - Shell features (pipes, redirection) available\n376: - Familiar syntax\n377: \n378: **Cons**:\n379: - Security risks (shell injection attacks)\n380: - Harder to control resource limits accurately\n381: - Additional attack surface\n382: - Non-deterministic behavior across shells\n383: \n384: **Decision**: Use direct execve-style execution for better security and control.\n385: \n386: ### Alternative 3: Container-based Execution\n387: \n388: **Approach**: Spawn a new container for each command\n389: \n390: **Pros**:\n391: - Strong isolation\n392: - Built-in resource limits via cgroups\n393: - Clean environment per command\n394: \n395: **Cons**:\n396: - High overhead (container startup latency)\n397: - Requires container runtime access\n398: - Complex orchestration\n399: - Overkill for simple command execution\n400: \n401: **Decision**: Use process-level isolation with proper limits for lower latency; container isolation is handled at the sandbox pod level (AR-005).\n402: \n403: ## Testing Strategy\n404: \n405: ### Unit Tests\n406: \n407: 1. **TestPicoD_Run_Success**: Basic command execution\n408: 2. **TestPicoD_Run_Timeout**: Command exceeds timeout\n409: 3. **TestPicoD_Run_OOM**: Command exceeds memory limit\n410: 4. **TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled**: Context cancellation\n411: 5. **TestPicoD_OutputCapture**: Stdout/stderr capture\n412: 6. **TestPicoD_SecurityValidation**: Invalid commands rejected\n413: 7. **TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate**: Resource limit validation\n414: 8. **TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate**: Security options validation\n415: 9. **TestPicoD_WithOptions**: Functional options pattern\n416: 10. **TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes**: Error type classification\n417: \n418: ### Integration Tests\n419: \n420: 1. **TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full execution flow\n421: 2. **TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent**: Multiple concurrent commands\n422: 3. **TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits**: Verify limits are enforced\n423: 4. **TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming**: Output streaming functionality\n424: 5. **TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling**: Process signal handling\n425: \n426: ## Acceptance Criteria\n427: \n428: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n429: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n430: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n431: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n432: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n433: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n434: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n435: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n436: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n437: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n438: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n439: \n440: ## References\n441: \n442: - Sandbox Infrastructure: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md`\n443: - Session Storage: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`\n444: - Valkey Storage: `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`\n445: - PicoD Spec: `code-execution/spec.md`\n446: - PicoD Design: `code-execution/design.md`\n447: - Client-Go: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 447 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n\nThis implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md","time":{"start":1775891141422,"end":1775891141440}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891141444,"sessionID":"ses_284a3f4d3ffe8bFOTfB7U7JhyS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b5c48c90011FcZrB854rCk9b","messageID":"msg_d7b5c38f90014Sja2hQKu99nyS","sessionID":"ses_284a3f4d3ffe8bFOTfB7U7JhyS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_eb89dae3eda84ddfa35333e4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-039 — Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod)\n2: \n3: ## 1. Purpose\n4: \n5: 为 `pkg/router`、`pkg/store` 和 `pkg/picod` 模块编写全面的 Go 单元测试，确保代码质量、可维护性和可靠性。\n6: \n7: 本提案针对 AR-039 需求，覆盖以下核心组件：\n8: - **Router**: 路由管理、反向代理、健康检查、JWT 认证\n9: - **Store**: Redis/Valkey 存储后端、会话管理、过期/ inactive 清理\n10: - **PicoD**: 沙箱执行器、文件系统、资源限制、安全选项\n11: \n12: ## 2. Scope\n13: \n14: ### 2.1 In Scope\n15: \n16: | 模块 | 文件 | 优先级 | 测试类型 | 当前状态 |\n17: |------|------|--------|----------|----------|\n18: | **pkg/router** | | | | |\n19: | | `router.go` | P0 | 单元测试 | 部分覆盖 |\n20: | | `handler.go` | P0 | 单元测试 | 部分覆盖 |\n21: | | `resolver.go` | P0 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n22: | | `health.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n23: | | `session_handler.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 需要补充 |\n24: | | `session_resolver.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 需要补充 |\n25: | | `config.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 需要补充 |\n26: | | `types.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 需要补充 |\n27: | | `handlers/token.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 需要补充 |\n28: | | `handlers/refresh.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 需要补充 |\n29: | | `handlers/revoke.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 需要补充 |\n30: | | `middleware/auth.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n31: | | `middleware/session_middleware.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n32: | | `blacklist/blacklist.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n33: | | `auth/jwt.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 需要补充 |\n34: | **pkg/store** | | | | |\n35: | | `store.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 部分覆盖 |\n36: | | `store_redis.go` | P0 | 单元测试 + mock | 已有测试 |\n37: | | `store_valkey.go` | P0 | 单元测试 + mock | 已有测试 |\n38: | | `codec.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n39: | | `singleton.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n40: | **pkg/picod** | | | | |\n41: | | `picod.go` | P0 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n42: | | `executor.go` | P0 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n43: | | `filesystem.go` | P0 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n44: | | `config.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n45: | | `jwt.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n46: | | `middleware.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n47: | | `security.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n48: | | `limits.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n49: | | `quota.go` | P1 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n50: | | `process.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n51: | | `output.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n52: | | `path.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n53: | | `fileinfo.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n54: | | `errors.go` | P2 | 单元测试 | 已有测试 |\n55: \n56: ### 2.2 Out of Scope\n57: \n58: - E2E 测试（由单独的测试计划覆盖）\n59: - 性能/负载测试\n60: - Valkey 集成测试（已有 `store_valkey_integration_test.go`）\n61: - PicoD 集成测试（已有 `integration_test.go`）\n62: \n63: ## 3. Impact Analysis\n64: \n65: ### 3.1 代码依赖\n66: \n67: ```\n68: pkg/router/\n69: ├── router.go              → 依赖 k8s client-go, informer, cache\n70: ├── handler.go             → 依赖 httputil, handlers\n71: ├── resolver.go            → 依赖 url parsing, routes\n72: ├── health.go              → 依赖 http client\n73: ├── session_handler.go     → 依赖 http\n74: ├── session_resolver.go    → 依赖 cache, informer\n75: ├── config.go              → 依赖 rest.Config\n76: ├── types.go               → 纯数据类型\n77: ├── handlers/\n78: │   ├── token.go           → 依赖 auth.JWTAuthenticator\n79: │   ├── refresh.go         → 依赖 auth.JWTAuthenticator\n80: │   └── revoke.go          → 依赖 auth.JWTAuthenticator\n81: ├── middleware/\n82: │   ├── auth.go            → 依赖 auth\n83: │   └── session_middleware.go → 依赖 http\n84: ├── blacklist/\n85: │   └── blacklist.go       → 纯工具，已有测试\n86: └── auth/\n87:     └── jwt.go             → 依赖 golang-jwt/jwt/v5\n88: \n89: pkg/store/\n90: ├── store.go               → 接口定义\n91: ├── store_redis.go         → 依赖 go-redis/v9\n92: ├── store_valkey.go        → 依赖 go-redis/v9\n93: ├── codec.go               → 纯工具函数\n94: └── singleton.go           → 依赖 store interface\n95: \n96: pkg/picod/\n97: ├── picod.go               → 依赖 executor, filesystem\n98: ├── executor.go            → 依赖 os/exec, context\n99: ├── filesystem.go          → 依赖 os, io/fs\n100: ├── config.go              → 依赖 encoding/json\n101: ├── jwt.go                 → 依赖 golang-jwt/jwt/v5\n102: ├── middleware.go          → 依赖 http\n103: ├── security.go            → 依赖 os/exec\n104: ├── limits.go              → 依赖 syscall\n105: ├── quota.go               → 依赖 os\n106: ├── process.go             → 依赖 os/exec\n107: ├── output.go              → 纯工具函数\n108: ├── path.go                → 依赖 filepath\n109: ├── fileinfo.go            → 依赖 io/fs\n110: └── errors.go              → 纯工具函数\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ### 3.2 测试基础设施需求\n114: \n115: 1. **Router 测试**:\n116:    - Mock kubernetes client 和 informer\n117:    - Mock HTTP server/client\n118:    - Mock JWT authenticator\n119:    - Test fixtures for RouteEntry, HealthStatus\n120: \n121: 2. **Store 测试**:\n122:    - Mock Redis client (使用 go-redis 的 Mock 或 mock 库)\n123:    - Test fixtures for SandboxInfo\n124: \n125: 3. **PicoD 测试**:\n126:    - 已有多数测试覆盖\n127:    - 需要补充边缘场景测试\n128: \n129: ### 3.3 预期工作量\n130: \n131: | 阶段 | 内容 | 预估时间 |\n132: |------|------|----------|\n133: | Phase 1 | Router 核心：router.go, handler.go | 8h |\n134: | Phase 2 | Router 扩展：resolver.go, health.go, session_*.go | 6h |\n135: | Phase 3 | Router Handlers: token.go, refresh.go, revoke.go | 4h |\n136: | Phase 4 | Router Auth/Middleware: auth/jwt.go, middleware/*.go | 4h |\n137: | Phase 5 | Store: store_redis.go, store_valkey.go (mock) | 6h |\n138: | Phase 6 | PicoD 补充测试：executor.go, security.go, limits.go | 4h |\n139: | Phase 7 | 集成测试 + 覆盖率分析 | 4h |\n140: | **总计** | | **36h** |\n141: \n142: ## 4. Alternatives Considered\n143: \n144: ### 4.1 方案 A: 使用 Mock 框架 (推荐用于 Store)\n145: \n146: **描述**: 使用 `gomock` 或 `testify/mock` 为 Redis client 和 kubernetes informer 生成 mock 实现\n147: \n148: **优点**:\n149: - 灵活控制返回值和行为\n150: - 可验证调用顺序和次数\n151: - 无需真实连接 Redis/K8s\n152: \n153: **缺点**:\n154: - 需要维护 mock 代码\n155: - mock 行为可能与真实实现不一致\n156: \n157: **采用原因**: Store 层需要 mock Redis client；Router 需要 mock informer\n158: \n159: ### 4.2 方案 B: 使用 Fake Clients (推荐用于 Router)\n160: \n161: **描述**: 使用 kubernetes client-go 提供的 fake clientset 和 informer\n162: \n163: **优点**:\n164: - 与真实 client 行为一致\n165: - 官方支持，无需额外依赖\n166: - 支持 informer/cache 相关测试\n167: \n168: **缺点**:\n169: - 部分场景需要手动管理 indexer\n170: - 无法模拟所有 API server 错误场景\n171: \n172: **采用原因**: Router 依赖 k8s informer，使用 fake clients 是社区标准做法\n173: \n174: ### 4.3 方案 C: 使用 Testcontainers (可选用于集成测试)\n175: \n176: **描述**: 使用 testcontainers-go 启动真实的 Redis 容器进行测试\n177: \n178: **优点**:\n179: - 最接近真实环境\n180: - 可测试真实 Redis 行为\n181: \n182: **缺点**:\n183: - 测试执行慢（需要启动容器）\n184: - 依赖 Docker\n185: - 不适合快速迭代的单元测试\n186: \n187: **不采用原因**: 已有 `store_valkey_integration_test.go` 覆盖集成测试场景\n188: \n189: ## 5. Test Strategy\n190: \n191: ### 5.1 测试分层\n192: \n193: ```\n194: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n195: │      Integration Tests              │  ← testcontainers (可选)\n196: ├─────────────────────────────────────┤\n197: │    Unit Tests (Fake Clients)        │  ← Router 主要测试层\n198: ├─────────────────────────────────────┤\n199: │    Unit Tests (Mock Clients)        │  ← Store 主要测试层\n200: ├─────────────────────────────────────┤\n201: │    Unit Tests (Pure Functions)      │  ← PicoD 基础测试\n202: └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ### 5.2 覆盖率目标\n206: \n207: - **Line Coverage**: ≥ 80%\n208: - **Branch Coverage**: ≥ 70%\n209: - **核心模块** (router/*, store/*): ≥ 85%\n210: \n211: ### 5.3 测试命名规范\n212: \n213: ```go\n214: // 格式：Test[FunctionName][Scenario]_[ExpectedResult]\n215: func TestRouter_NewRouter_NilConfig_ReturnsError(t *testing.T)\n216: func TestHandler_ServeHTTP_AuthRequired_NoToken_Returns401(t *testing.T)\n217: func TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilSandbox_ReturnsError(t *testing.T)\n218: func TestExecutor_Run_CommandNotFound_ReturnsExecutionError(t *testing.T)\n219: ```\n220: \n221: ### 5.4 表驱动测试模板\n222: \n223: ```go\n224: func TestXxx(t *testing.T) {\n225:     tests := []struct {\n226:         name        string\n227:         input       InputType\n228:         expected    ExpectedType\n229:         expectError bool\n230:     }{\n231:         {\"scenario1\", input1, expected1, false},\n232:         {\"scenario2\", input2, expected2, true},\n233:     }\n234:     \n235:     for _, tt := range tests {\n236:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n237:             // test logic\n238:         })\n239:     }\n240: }\n241: ```\n242: \n243: ## 6. Test Cases Detail\n244: \n245: ### 6.1 pkg/router/router.go (P0)\n246: \n247: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n248: |-----------|----------|\n249: | `NewRouter()` | nil config, invalid kubeconfig, success |\n250: | `SetInformers()` | nil informers, valid informers, event handler registration |\n251: | `onAgentRuntimeAdd()` | not exposed, no backend URL, valid add |\n252: | `onAgentRuntimeUpdate()` | update triggers add logic |\n253: | `onAgentRuntimeDelete()` | direct delete, tombstone delete, invalid object |\n254: | `onCodeInterpreter*()` | similar to AgentRuntime |\n255: | `shouldExpose()` | label present/absent/false |\n256: | `extractBackendURLFromStatus()` | nil ref, empty name, valid ref |\n257: | `Start()` | server startup, error handling |\n258: | `Shutdown()` | graceful shutdown, token blacklist stop |\n259: | `GetRoute()` | found, not found |\n260: | `ListRoutes()` | empty, multiple routes |\n261: | `AddRoute()` / `RemoveRoute()` | add/remove operations |\n262: \n263: ### 6.2 pkg/router/handler.go (P0)\n264: \n265: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n266: |-----------|----------|\n267: | `NewHandler()` | with/without auth |\n268: | `ServeHTTP()` | auth endpoints, regular proxy |\n269: | `ProxyRequest()` | valid backend, invalid URL, error handler |\n270: | `AddForwardingHeaders()` | with/without TLS, client IP extraction |\n271: | `writeError()` | various error types, status codes |\n272: \n273: ### 6.3 pkg/router/resolver.go (P1)\n274: \n275: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n276: |-----------|----------|\n277: | `NewResolver()` | initialization |\n278: | `Resolve()` | exact match, prefix match, not found |\n279: | Invalid resource type, malformed path |\n280: \n281: ### 6.4 pkg/router/health.go (P1)\n282: \n283: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n284: |-----------|----------|\n285: | `NewHealthChecker()` | initialization |\n286: | `Start()` / `Stop()` | lifecycle |\n287: | `checkHealth()` | healthy, unhealthy, timeout |\n288: | `tick()` | single check |\n289: \n290: ### 6.5 pkg/router/session_handler.go (P1)\n291: \n292: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n293: |-----------|----------|\n294: | `ServeHTTP()` | session lookup, proxy |\n295: \n296: ### 6.6 pkg/router/session_resolver.go (P1)\n297: \n298: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n299: |-----------|----------|\n300: | `Resolve()` | informer-based resolution |\n301: \n302: ### 6.7 pkg/router/handlers/*.go (P1)\n303: \n304: | 文件 | 测试场景 |\n305: |------|----------|\n306: | `token.go` | valid request, invalid credentials, missing fields |\n307: | `refresh.go` | valid refresh, expired token, invalid token |\n308: | `revoke.go` | valid revoke, missing token |\n309: \n310: ### 6.8 pkg/router/auth/jwt.go (P1)\n311: \n312: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n313: |-----------|----------|\n314: | `NewJWTAuthenticator()` | valid/invalid config |\n315: | `Authenticate()` | valid token, expired, invalid signature |\n316: | `GenerateToken()` / `RefreshToken()` / `RevokeToken()` | respective operations |\n317: \n318: ### 6.9 pkg/store/store_redis.go (P0)\n319: \n320: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n321: |-----------|----------|\n322: | `makeRedisOptions()` | missing env, password required/not required |\n323: | `NewRedisStore()` | initialization |\n324: | `Ping()` | success, failure |\n325: | `GetSandboxBySessionID()` | found, not found, error |\n326: | `StoreSandbox()` | nil sandbox, zero expiry, success, duplicate |\n327: | `UpdateSandbox()` | nil, not found, success |\n328: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` | success |\n329: | `ListExpiredSandboxes()` | limit <= 0, found, none |\n330: | `ListInactiveSandboxes()` | similar to expired |\n331: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` | empty sessionID, not found, success |\n332: | `Close()` | cleanup |\n333: \n334: ### 6.10 pkg/store/store_valkey.go (P0)\n335: \n336: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n337: |-----------|----------|\n338: | Similar to Redis store tests | |\n339: \n340: ### 6.11 pkg/store/codec.go (P2)\n341: \n342: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n343: |-----------|----------|\n344: | `marshalSandboxInfo()` / `unmarshalSandboxInfo()` | valid/invalid data |\n345: \n346: ### 6.12 pkg/store/singleton.go (P2)\n347: \n348: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n349: |-----------|----------|\n350: | `GetStore()` / `InitStore()` / `CloseStore()` | singleton pattern |\n351: \n352: ### 6.13 pkg/picod/executor.go (P0)\n353: \n354: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n355: |-----------|----------|\n356: | `NewExecutor()` | initialization |\n357: | `Run()` | command not found, timeout, OOM, success |\n358: | `Start()` | similar to Run |\n359: | `limitedBuffer.Write()` / `Bytes()` | within limit, over limit |\n360: \n361: ### 6.14 pkg/picod/security.go (P1)\n362: \n363: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n364: |-----------|----------|\n365: | `ValidateCommand()` | allowed/blocked commands, paths |\n366: \n367: ### 6.15 pkg/picod/limits.go (P1)\n368: \n369: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n370: |-----------|----------|\n371: | `DefaultResourceLimits()` | defaults |\n372: | `Apply()` | set limits on command |\n373: \n374: ### 6.16 pkg/picod/quota.go (P1)\n375: \n376: | 函数/方法 | 测试场景 |\n377: |-----------|----------|\n378: | `DefaultFileQuota()` | defaults |\n379: | `CheckFileSize()` / `CheckTotalSize()` | within/over quota |\n380: \n381: ## 7. Implementation Plan\n382: \n383: ### Phase 1: Router Core (8h)\n384: ```\n385: - [ ] router/router_test.go (补充覆盖)\n386: - [ ] router/handler_test.go (补充覆盖)\n387: - [ ] router/types_test.go\n388: - [ ] router/config_test.go\n389: ```\n390: \n391: ### Phase 2: Router Extended (6h)\n392: ```\n393: - [ ] router/resolver_test.go (补充覆盖)\n394: - [ ] router/health_test.go (补充覆盖)\n395: - [ ] router/session_handler_test.go\n396: - [ ] router/session_resolver_test.go\n397: ```\n398: \n399: ### Phase 3: Router Handlers (4h)\n400: ```\n401: - [ ] router/handlers/token_test.go\n402: - [ ] router/handlers/refresh_test.go\n403: - [ ] router/handlers/revoke_test.go\n404: ```\n405: \n406: ### Phase 4: Router Auth (4h)\n407: ```\n408: - [ ] router/auth/jwt_test.go\n409: - [ ] router/middleware/auth_test.go (补充覆盖)\n410: - [ ] router/middleware/session_middleware_test.go (补充覆盖)\n411: ```\n412: \n413: ### Phase 5: Store (6h)\n414: ```\n415: - [ ] store/store_redis_test.go (补充 mock 测试)\n416: - [ ] store/store_valkey_test.go (补充 mock 测试)\n417: - [ ] store/store_test.go (补充覆盖)\n418: ```\n419: \n420: ### Phase 6: PicoD Supplement (4h)\n421: ```\n422: - [ ] picod/executor_test.go (补充边缘场景)\n423: - [ ] picod/security_test.go (补充覆盖)\n424: - [ ] picod/limits_test.go (补充覆盖)\n425: - [ ] picod/quota_test.go (补充覆盖)\n426: ```\n427: \n428: ### Phase 7: Integration (4h)\n429: ```\n430: - [ ] 运行测试覆盖率：go test -coverprofile=cover.out ./pkg/...\n431: - [ ] 生成覆盖率报告：go tool cover -html=cover.out\n432: - [ ] 确保覆盖率达标\n433: - [ ] 修复 failing tests\n434: ```\n435: \n436: ## 8. Success Criteria\n437: \n438: 1. ✅ 所有新增测试通过\n439: 2. ✅ 整体覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n440: 3. ✅ 核心模块覆盖率 ≥ 85%\n441: 4. ✅ 无数据竞争（`go test -race` 通过）\n442: 5. ✅ 测试可重复运行（无状态污染）\n443: 6. ✅ CI/CD 集成通过\n444: \n445: ## 9. Dependencies\n446: \n447: - Go 1.21+\n448: - Kubernetes client-go v0.34.1\n449: - github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n450: - github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\n451: - github.com/stretchr/testify (testing)\n452: - github.com/golang/mock (optional, for mocking)\n453: \n454: ## 10. References\n455: \n456: - [Kubernetes Testing Guide](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-testing/testing.md)\n457: - [client-go testing](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go/tree/master/testing)\n458: - [go-redis testing](https://github.com/redis/go-redis/tree/master)\n459: - `pkg/router/design.md` - Router 详细设计文档\n460: - `pkg/picod/design.md` - PicoD 详细设计文档\n461: - `deployment/client-go.md` - client-go 生成代码说明\n\n(End of file - total 461 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-039 — Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod)\n\n## 1. Purpose\n\n为 `pkg/router`、`pkg/store` 和 `pkg/picod` 模块编写全面的 Go 单元测试，确保代码质量、可维护性和可靠性。\n\n本提案针对 AR-039 需求，覆盖以下核心组件：\n- **Router**: 路由管理、反向代理、健康检查、JWT 认证\n- **Store**: Redis/Valkey 存储后端、会话管理、过期/ inactive 清理\n- **PicoD**: 沙箱执行器、文件系统、资源限制、安全选项\n\n## 2. Scope\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n| 模块 | 文件 | 优先级 | 测试类型 | 当前状态 |\n|------|------|--------|----------|----------|\n| **pkg/router** | | | | |\n| | `router.go` | P0 | 单元测试 | 部分覆盖 |\n| | `handler.go` | P0 | 单元测试 | 部分覆盖 |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775891141426,"end":1775891141443}}}}
